{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":101710,"duration_api_ms":101681,"num_turns":3,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"269d0787-ccad-42b8-8e5e-3f865cc1f9ca","total_cost_usd":0.35408605,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25732,"cache_read_input_tokens":78821,"output_tokens":2721,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":25732,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":2721,"cacheReadInputTokens":78821,"cacheCreationInputTokens":25732,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2682805,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":17,"outputTokens":3938,"cacheReadInputTokens":25948,"cacheCreationInputTokens":50803,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.08580555000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Accept three amendments identifying real correctness gaps (struct duplication silent data loss, run_id matching gap preventing legitimate backfill, plan_hash provenance loss). Reject the debug_assert suggestion as purely stylistic with no correctness impact, and reject the legacy-repair objection because that code serves current crash recovery and idempotence needs, not just historical migration.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-21-cbb5ddb0","decision":"accept","rationale":"The fs.rs StartJournalDetails and CompletionJournalDetails structs independently redeclare the field set of their model.rs Payload counterparts. Since serde's default Deserialize behavior silently ignores unknown fields, adding a new field to the model's rendering payload without updating the fs adapter's parsing struct means the merge/repair path will parse the JSON, drop the new field, and re-render without it — a silent data loss bug. This is not speculative: the repair path is exercised on every idempotent journal append, so the risk is real and ongoing. Sharing the type or adding a sync assertion is a sound fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-21-5549be65","decision":"reject","rationale":"The amendment itself acknowledges details is always Some for BeadStarted events produced by this code. Returning None (skipping repair, allowing a fresh append) is reasonable fail-closed behavior for any hypothetical malformed row. A debug_assert only fires in debug builds and documents an invariant that is already enforced by construction — it doesn't identify a correctness bug or a plausible failure mode. The suggestion is a minor code hygiene improvement, not a defect warranting an amendment."},{"amendment_id":"fr-21-e0d6bb34","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real matching gap in the update_task_run flow. When a bead start is recorded before the controller knows the run_id, the entry is stored without one. When the completion arrives with the now-known run_id, the matching logic at lines 2984-3024 can reject the only valid open match because the run_id doesn't match (None vs Some). The backfill infrastructure at lines 3186-3209 already knows how to fill in run_id on a matched row, and started_at provides sufficient disambiguation. The matching phase just fails to route to it. This prevents legitimate same-attempt completion in a restart/late-binding scenario."},{"amendment_id":"fr-21-1c624db9","decision":"accept","rationale":"persist_plan computes and stores the canonical plan_hash in the milestone snapshot, but neither record_bead_start nor the update_task_run service path consult it as a fallback. They only forward the caller-supplied plan_hash, which may be None. The result is that TaskRunEntry rows can be written with plan_hash: None even though the service layer already has the active plan version available in the snapshot. This is a real provenance loss: lineage evidence should carry the plan linkage the system already knows about, rather than relying entirely on every caller to propagate it."},{"amendment_id":"fr-21-5c56671a","decision":"reject","rationale":"The cited code serves current operational needs, not just legacy migration. Named/runless fallback matching handles the real scenario where run_id is unknown at start time and arrives later (exactly the gap fr-21-e0d6bb34 describes). Attempt collapsing produces clean state views from partial writes after crashes. Journal row rewriting enables idempotent re-appends during restart recovery. Backfill helpers fill in run_id and plan_hash that become known after initial write. Removing this layer would regress crash recovery, restart safety, and idempotent replay — all current requirements. The amendment conflates partial-write repair with legacy data migration."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a66458df-e325-4ff5-9909-c0d73fb2c7af"}
